sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the execution of a Windows system binary that is usually located in the system folder from an uncommon location.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Patrick Bareiss, Anton Kutepov, oscd.community, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects creation of a new service via "sc" command or the powershell "new-service" cmdlet with suspicious binary paths

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=sc.exe; Hashes=SHA1=DA70DF7EF2F87BFEDBEA9FE53169B16E0CF4B12E,MD5=35AFDDBBF42372FF50809E87BBB88F0E,SHA256=3CE81FA5051C945F70953A70D71BE30708D7831B97A5C95070BF9972D6E9FCE2,IMPHASH=7EB6A79D09C556824451987988AA3078; Description=Service Control Manager Configuration Tool; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine="C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\software.exe"; CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\sc.exe" create weqpgkfj binPath= "C:\Windows\SysWOW64\weqpgkfj\iuczfsyw.exe /d\"C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\software.exe\"" type= own start= auto DisplayName= "wifi support"; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\software.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\sc.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Windows\system32\; OriginalFileName=svchost.exe; Hashes=SHA1=115878CFB730B1F2CB084CDC51FDD92E9B36F9A8,MD5=B96D1C078A724E31B6F98CDB999E47F6,SHA256=49FAB89D62923D68D5F9627C68110EF522A668730598C3B09CD74FBE8F3F3E62,IMPHASH=CD4B689577AA1EF0BEFC1F09C4682C67; Description=Host Process for Windows Services; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\weqpgkfj\iuczfsyw.exe /d"C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\software.exe"; CommandLine=svchost.exe; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\weqpgkfj\iuczfsyw.exe; IntegrityLevel=System; Image=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Firewall Rule Added Via Netsh.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the addition of a new rule to the Windows firewall via netsh

match_context.values: @{EventID=1; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul}
